caption: Table 1: Fraction of time (%) required for the UQ-guided methods to achieve comparable model performance as the original HPO methods do.
description: This table presents the efficiency gains achieved by the UQ-guided HPO methods compared to their original counterparts.  It shows the percentage of time each UQ-guided method (SH+, HB+, BOHB+, SS+) needed to reach a comparable model performance level as its original UQ-oblivious version (SH, HB, BOHB, SS) on two benchmark datasets (NAS-BENCH-201 and LCBench). Lower percentages indicate better efficiency.

caption: Table 2: Benchmark and Dataset information.
description: This table summarizes the datasets used in the experiments, including the number of hyperparameters, fidelity levels, and the sizes of training, validation, and test sets for each dataset.  It provides key details about the experimental setup and data characteristics for both Nas-Bench-201 and LCBench.
